are all working together,

116
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:53,730
this becomes really important
because I need my LLM

117
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:56,910
to be able to understand all that code.

118
00:04:56,910 --> 00:05:00,150
I need it to be able to
understand that code consistently.

119
00:05:00,150 --> 00:05:03,390
And I need it to be able
to produce similar results

120
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:06,750
for all 150 developers along the way.

121
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:10,080
It does me no good if the
non-deterministic nature

122
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:13,050
of the LLMs creates working solutions

123
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:14,910
for all 150 developers,

124
00:05:14,910 --> 00:05:17,910
but it does so in very incompatible ways,

125
00:05:17,910 --> 00:05:19,860
which is possible when you think about

126
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:23,280
the non-deterministic
aspects of generative AI.

127
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,990
So how do we do this at scale?

128
00:05:24,990 --> 00:05:27,930
How do we solve for
large development teams

129
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:31,620
and how do we solve for
large existing code bases?

130
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:33,840
The other piece is the idea of control.

131
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:35,640
We talked about, in the previous slide,

132
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:38,370
about this true collaboration concept,

133
00:05:38,370 --> 00:05:41,160
but that's not really what
we have in generative AI.

134
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,370
What we have in generative
AI is we take this prompt

135
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:47,730
that we kind of concoct and
and throw into the chat box,

136
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:51,780
