and fill in the blanks.

144
00:06:10,290 --> 00:06:11,580
And maybe it got it right,

145
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:13,830
maybe it chose the option
you would've chosen,

146
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:17,070
maybe it didn't, but now it's
up to you to figure that out.

147
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:18,900
And now you've got a 1,000 lines of code

148
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:21,120
that you've gotta go
and figure it out with.

149
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,110
And then the last piece

150
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:25,170
is when you take those
two factors together,

151
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:27,420
both of those negatively impact

152
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:29,130
the overall quality of the code.

153
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:31,920
What you're getting is code
that you don't really want.

154
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,530
It doesn't really do
what you wanted it to do,

155
00:06:34,530 --> 00:06:37,110
and it doesn't really do it
the way you wanted it to do.

156
00:06:37,110 --> 00:06:38,640
And it does it differently

157
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,800
for all the different
developers on your team,

158
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,510
which is not helpful.

159
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:45,870
So what we created for Kiro

160
00:06:45,870 --> 00:06:49,290
and what we tightly
integrated into the solution

161
00:06:49,290 --> 00:06:51,630
is something that we call
spec-driven development.

162
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:55,290
And it's a return back to first principles

163
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,610
of software development.

164
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:59,160
We don't bring a team of
developers into a room,

165
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:02,040
write four bullet points on a whiteboard,

166
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:05,400
and say, "Guys, we'll check
in on you in six months.

167
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,110
Let us know how it goes."

168
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:10,170
That would be chaos, and for good reason.

169
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:11,767
What we do is we step back and we say,

170
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:13,500
"All right, what are the requirements?

171
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,550
Let's detail those.

172
00:07:14,550 --> 00:07:15,780
Let's bring in our stakeholders,

173
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:18,900
let's bring in all the key
players and lay that out."

174
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,730
Then we say, "All right, well
these are the requirements.

175
00:07:20,730 --> 00:07:21,660
How are we gonna build this?"

176
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:23,617
And we build a design document and we say,

177
00:07:23,617 --> 00:07:25,650
"What are all of the
different design specs

178
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,000
and the technical details?"

179
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,987
And we lay all of those out

180
00:07:27,987 --> 00:07:30,150
and we bring in all the stakeholders.

181
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:30,983
And then we say,

182
00:07:30,983 --> 00:07:32,280
"All right, well, what
is the project plan?"

183
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,230
We build one of those fun Gantt charts

184
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:35,910
